---
source: crates/normalize/tests/cli_snapshots.rs
expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"analyze\", \"trace\"])"
---
Analyze codebase (health, complexity, security, duplicates, docs)

Usage: normalize analyze [OPTIONS] [target]

Arguments:
  [target]  Target file or directory

Options:
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -r, --root <root>                Root directory (defaults to current directory)
      --exclude <exclude>          Exclude paths matching pattern
      --only <only>                Include only paths matching pattern
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version

Commands:
  health             Run health analysis (file counts, complexity stats, large file warnings)
  all                Run all analysis passes
  summary            Auto-generated single-page codebase overview

Code quality:
  complexity-trend   Show complexity trend over git history
  length             Run function length analysis
  length-trend       Show function length trend over git history
  node-types         List node kinds and field names for a tree-sitter grammar

Module structure:
  density-trend      Show information density trend over git history

Repository:
  docs               Analyze documentation coverage

Graph analysis:
  architecture       Show architecture analysis (coupling, cycles, hubs)

Git history:
  coupling-clusters  Change-clusters: connected components of temporally coupled files
  activity           Analyze cross-repo activity over time
  repo-coupling      Analyze cross-repo coupling
  cross-repo-health  Rank repos by tech debt (churn + complexity + coupling)
  trend              Track health metrics over git history at regular intervals

Testing:
  test-gaps          Find untested public functions ranked by risk
  test-ratio-trend   Show test ratio trend over git history

Security:
  security           Run security analysis

Diff:
  skeleton-diff      Show structural changes between a base ref and HEAD
